&lt;p&gt;The Delivery Truck Driver is responsible for the safe operation of the company’s vehicle. This role is responsible for all functions related to the vehicle, including the pre-trip report (DVIR), ensuring the truck is loaded properly, the material is secured to the truck, delivery of materials to the customer location, and processing of all customer delivery paperwork.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;JOB DESCRIPTION&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely operate a heavy-load truck.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all material is properly secured at the beginning of the shift and continuously monitor after each delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that all customer supporting paperwork is completed and returned at the end of each shift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect, document, and properly secure money received to ensure alignment with customer paperwork.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report any issues or incidents related to material damage or customer matters to dispatch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform the daily truck inspection, pre- and post-trip (DVIR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seek advice and guidance on non-routine or problem areas from supervisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform and document inspections to ensure truck and equipment are kept in good condition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Basic Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of truck driving experience with a proven track record of safe driving.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in driving automatic transmission trucks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possession of a commercial driver&#39;s license (type A or B)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capability to operate a gate lift.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in operating an electric pallet jack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in handling commercial and residential deliveries.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to service all region’s distribution centers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel is required for this position.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful completion of a pre-employment drug test and background check is mandatory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;WordSection2&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of DOT rules and regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5 years of forklift experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5 years of truck driving experience with a proven track record of safe driving.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
